<p>Is it possible to make sitecore experience editor ribbon button trigger <code>.aspx</code> page in pop up window? It was possible before <code>speak-ui</code> was introduced by assigning a command to the button's <code>click</code> field.</p>  <p>There is a lot of tutorials describing how to use XML controls (e.g. <a href="http://jockstothecore.com/sitecore-8-ribbon-button-transfiguration/" rel="nofollow">http://jockstothecore.com/sitecore-8-ribbon-button-transfiguration/</a>) but I can't find any information about triggering <code>.aspx</code> page.</p>  <p>My command looks like this: <code>&lt;command name="item:showDashboard" type="Sitecore.Starterkit.customcode.Reports, MyProject" /&gt;</code></p>